name: Coin Partitions 2
description:
let P(n) be a function that represents the number of ways that n coins can be partitioned. For example, 5 coins can be partitioned in seven different ways:
ooooo
oooo o
ooo oo
ooo o o
oo oo o
oo o o o
o o o o o

You will be given an input N for which you must print p(N). Each N given will be between 1000 and 5000
